`crates/` is a Cargo workspace whose sole current member is `steno`, the theory-to-dictionary compiler and its supporting tooling/tests. Depending on the workspace at this level gets you nothing beyond what `steno/` itself exports — there's no cross-crate glue, shared types, or workspace-level code to track yet.

Any editor working here works entirely inside `steno/`; its rollup covers the pipeline staging, the corpus-coupled test suite, and the two crate-spanning invariants (editor-profile semantics, terminal-flag classification) that actually need cross-file awareness. There's nothing at the `crates/` level itself — no shared config, no sibling crate to keep in sync — so this file has no independent contract to state beyond pointing into `steno/`.

No `intent.md` is present for this directory, so no divergence check applies.